OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F101A1781470070
OL,1,W~{4{$~k4j5k7 j5j5~sjw=hw1~{4oz%G2/3
OL,2,W/*%/.!+.!+.!*% "-/.!+,*-'*% /*%/*%V,,,,
OL,3,CTeletext on the web
OL,4,C
OL,5,GWebfaxFis a tribute to teletext
OL,6,Fservices such asGCeefaxFandGORACLE.
OL,7,F
OL,8,FThanks to software written byGPeter
OL,9,GKwanFwe're able to keep teletext alive
OL,10,Ffor a new audience on the internet.
OL,12,FLike its predecessors,GWebfaxFoffers a
OL,13,Fmix of content, such as news, sport,
OL,14,Fweather, TV/radio guides and features.
OL,16,GWebfaxFis managed byGThe TV RoomFusing
OL,17,Fsoftware built and maintained in-house.
OL,19,FAdditionallyGNathan DaneFprovides
OL,20,Fsolutions for news, sport and weather
OL,21,Fcontent.FThe Teletext Viewer mechanism
OL,22,Fis produced byGAlistair Cree.
OL,23,Vppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
